books.title: Queen of the Universe
books.author: Pia Wurtzbach
books.description: What happens when climbing the ladder of success means compromising everything you believe in…including yourself? This debut novel by an actress and pageant title holder gives a window into the hidden rungs of that ladder, and on the pain that comes with slipping and falling. Cleo is young, beautiful, talented and--until lately--lucky in love. But in the cut-throat world of international beauty competitions, she has to make the biggest decision of her life.
books.review: This book is seriously a blast! If you're into a super relatable character suddenly becoming ruler of everything, with loads of wild cosmic adventures, twists, and maybe some laughs, you've gotta read this. It's a quick, fun ride that totally immerses you in its universe!

books.title: It Ends With Us
books.author: Colleen Hoover
books.description: The story follows florist Lily Bloom navigates a tumultuous romantic relationship with neurosurgeon Ryle Kincaid while grappling with the shadow of her abusive childhood and the return of her high school sweetheart, Atlas Corrigan.The story explores themes of domestic violence, emotional abuse, and the struggle to break generational patterns of trauma.
books.review: It Ends With Us is one of those books that just sticks with you. It kicks off like a super sweet romance between Lily Bloom and Ryle Kincaid, totally drawing you in. But then, whoa, it dives deep into the messy, tough stuff of domestic abuse, and it really makes you get why it's so incredibly hard when love and pain get all tangled up. Plus, Lily's old journal entries from when she was a kid give you all these emotional insights into how her past messed with her present, and Hoover's writing, told right from Lily's perspective, pulls you right into Lily's journey of heartbreak and resilience.

books.title: Gone Girl
books.author: Gillian Flynn
books.description: Gone Girl by Gillian Flynn is a psychological thriller that follows the disappearance of Amy Dunne on her and her husband Nick's fifth wedding anniversary. The novel explores themes of marriage, media, and the unreliable nature of memory and perception. Nick becomes the prime suspect as Amy goes missing, and the story unfolds through alternating perspectives, revealing secrets and layers of deception.
books.review: This book is insane  in the best possible way! If you love thrillers that mess with your head and make you question EVERYTHING, this is it. Amy disappears, Nick looks guilty, and the whole book is just a wild, twisted ride trying to figure out what the heck actually happened. It's totally gripping, super dark, and will leave you thinking about it long after you're done. Seriously, prepare to be mind-blown!

books.title: The Cabin at the End of the World
books.author: Paul G. Tremblay
books.description: A suspenseful novel about a family vacationing at a remote cabin in New Hampshire who are confronted by strangers who claim to need their help to save the world.
books.review: This book is stressful in the best possible way, if you're into that! Imagine a family vacation in a remote cabin, then strangers show up with a terrifying, impossible choice to prevent the apocalypse. It's a super intense, claustrophobic thriller that'll keep you on the edge of your seat the whole time, making you wonder what you'd do. Definitely a wild, unsettling ride!

books.title: The Game of Thrones
books.author: George R. R. Martin
books.description: A sweeping epic fantasy novel that follows the intricate political machinations of numerous noble houses vying for control of the Seven Kingdoms in the fictional world of Westeros.
books.review: This book is where all the epic fantasy craziness begins! If you like huge worlds, tons of characters, intense political fights, and shocking twists (seriously, prepare yourself!), then jump into this one. It's the start of an amazing, super addictive journey with dragons, ice zombies, and loads of drama.

books.title: The Hunger Games
books.author: Suzanne Collins
books.description: The Hunger Games is a 2008 dystopian young adult novel by the American writer Suzanne Collins. It is written in the perspective of 16-year-old Katniss Everdeen, who lives in the future, post-apocalyptic nation of Panem in North America. The Capitol, a highly advanced metropolis, exercises political control over the rest of the nation. The Hunger Games is an annual event in which one boy and one girl aged 12–18 from each of the twelve districts surrounding the Capitol are selected by lottery to compete in a televised battle royale to the death.
books.review: Hunger games is one of my favourite! its a total ride.It's fast-paced, full of action, and makes you think about bigger stuff too. You'll be hooked from page one, wondering if she'll make it out alive!

books.title: People We Meet on Vacation
books.author: Emily Henry
books.description: Poppy and Alex. Alex and Poppy. They have nothing in common. She’s a wild child; he wears khakis. She has insatiable wanderlust; he prefers to stay home with a book. And somehow, ever since a fateful car share home from college many years ago, they are the very best of friends. For most of the year they live far apart—she’s in New York City and he’s in their small hometown—but every summer for a decade, they have taken one glorious week of vacation together.
books.review: Amazing book, I fell in love the moment I read the first chapter!

books.title: The Knight and the Moth
books.author: Rachel Gillig
books.description: From BookTok sensation and NYT bestselling author Rachel Gillig, comes the next big romantasy phenomenon: a gothic, mist-cloaked tale of a prophetess who is forced beyond the safety of her cloister on an impossible quest to defeat the gods with the one knight whose future is beyond her sight.
books.review: Not yet read so I dont know.

books.title: A Treachery of Swans
books.author: A.B. Poranek
books.description:
An enthralling sapphic retelling of Swan Lake, for fans of Allison Saft and V.E Schwab.

Magic has long been outlawed in Auréal . Odile has always known she’d be the one to restore it.

Raised by a sorcerer, Odile has spent years preparing for the heist of a lifetime. It’s perfectly simple. Impersonate a princess, infiltrate the palace, steal the king's enchanted crown and restore magic to the kingdom.

But when the King is unexpectedly murdered, she’s forced to recruit the help of Marie d'Odette, the real princess, and the two begin to unravel a web of lies and deceit that leaves Odile uncertain of who to trust.
